gomodel:SYNGO_1590  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: eIF4G (G1 isoform according to cited paper) is present in the dendritic compartment of primary hippocampal neurons and juxtaposed to synaptophysin.\n\n26/9/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \" Some, but not all, apposing red/green puncta pairs apparently overlapped to some degree, evidenced by narrow yellow interface areas. Because green puncta identify axonal presynaptic specializations, it is concluded that such apposing red clusters correlate with postsynaptic dendritic compartments.\". Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons were presumably prepared from E18 rats." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1590" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

